        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 2:35PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles west of Meeker, or on the northwest corner of the Lee fire
burns scar.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation and
outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Rio Blanco
County.

This includes Colorado 64 between mile markers 59 and 68.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
